OL,6,FHe was fined #575, pleading guilty in
OL,7,Fthe case that was escalated to Jersey
OL,8,FMagistrate's Court after Deputy Ozouf
OL,9,Ffailed three times to attend an
OL,10,Fenquiry about the matter at his local
OL,11,FParish Hall.
OL,13,FHe was found to have breached the
OL,14,FStates' Code of Conduct on multiple
OL,15,Foccasions, including his ability to
OL,16,Fuphold the law, with the Privileges
OL,17,Fand Procedures Committee recommending
OL,18,Fa 28-day suspension without pay.
